Title: Remnants Author name: Artist name: Genre: J2, RPS Pairing: Jared/Jensen, past Jared/Chad Michael Murray Rating: R Word count: 29,337 Warnings/Spoilers: Minor character death, natural disaster, lots of snark. Summary: A lost notebook lands on the lawn of a lost family. Its contents--filled with pictures, drawings, lyrics, and descriptions of the road trip of a lifetime--persuade a shattered soul to take a chance and take the same trip. Will finding the owner of the book give Jared a second chance at love? Or was it all just a waste of gas?
ONE | TWO | THREE | FOUR | FIVE | SIX | SEVEN | EIGHT | | ART POST | NOTES & ACKNOWLEDGMENTS | PDF & SOUNDTRACK |

Notes and Acknowledgements

This year's Big Bang is brought to you by the letter E for escapism and the letter W for weheartit.com. First off, I'd like to say that had I known about the storms that have recently ripped through the southern U.S., I would have never written a story about tornados. That being said, I'm not mother nature and alas, here we are. This story came--as most of my stories do--from equal parts visual inspiration and a written prompt. Visually this year, the pictures that kept popping up on weheartit caused me to daydream about driving across the U.S. in a beat up old car, barefoot and smoking clove cigarettes (which actually taste disgusting, if you must know). The image greatly helped shape the landscape of the piece and reminded me of what certain places should look and feel like in the story. I'll include a link to the pictures I saved down below so you can peruse them while you read. The written prompt was a simple, solitary word:

Lost

As many of you will notice upon reading the fic, the journal is not the only thing that's lost. Jared turns into something of a temporary nomad after losing his family and until he reaches NYC and starts his new life, he too is lost. One could even argue that Jensen took the trip to find himself. It takes a series of different experiences, new faces, and ever-changing hotel rooms for Jared to heal and grow out of the tragedy that occurs at the beginning of the story, finding a new path in life and with it, a new love. I myself have never made this trip, so to any of you who live in the cities mentioned, I apologize if my descriptions are innacurate. I hope I haven't portrayed any place in a bad light, and if I have, it was merely for the sake of comedy and not because I truly hate your town/city/state. As for the tone of the fic, I will readily admit to having been immersed in my second read-through of Warren Ellis', Crooked Little Vein, which is a book far more hilarious and demented than I ever came close to in this fic. If you've got some cajones, have a read. It's worth it! I tried to make everything a little less formal than last year's story, language-wise, more snark and cussing than in Zzyzx. Mindy, Wendall, and even Jensen all had a hand in this, bringing different voices to the fic and making it more of a fun read than last year's, in my opinion. The secondary characters may not be familiar to everyone, so for the sake of visual aid, here is who I had in mind for the following characters:

Zooey Deschanel as Mindy Sharon Gless as Donna Christian Kane as Chris
Wendall is every redneck with dirty clothes and a yellowing beard you've ever seen at Walmart. Just sayin'. The other obvious inspiration for this fic was the movie, Elizabethtown, which follows a similar path, though the reason for the trip in the movie is based more on professional failure and natural death, than mother nature pulling the carpet out from under your feet. The idea of a scrapbook guide of sorts really appealed to all the other visual stimuli that I was immersed in when I first started writing, and it also fit hand in hand with my need to create a soundtrack for (almost) every story I write. If you haven't seen the movie, I highly reccomend it! As my beta wants me to point out, this fic was originally supposed to be MUCH longer than what you have as a final product. Real life got in the way, with my focus shifting from writing to getting fit. A new fandom (Hawaii Five-0) didn't help matters, and the muse ran away with any inspiration I had for longer than I care to admit in public. She came back at the very last minute though, and that's what matters. There are some 'missing' scenes that I may or may not write out in the future. All depends on what happens next month when all the shows start up again. ;) Huge thank yous go to my wonderful and ever-patient beta, . I threw her for a loop this year, and as always, she gave me sound, unbiased advice. Her critiques, and sharp eye is why this fic looks as polished as it is. My art this year was done by the awesome who put a lot of hard work into the gorgeous visuals that accompany the fic. Without both of you, this would be just another average J2 fic, so thank you both for making it incredible! If you guys have any questions about the fic, please don't hesitate to ask, either here or in the comments of the fic itself! Thanks for reading!
Remnants @ weheartit

A plot bunny has recently fallen into my lap and dragged me off to Writersville with no hope of returning any time soon. The only problem is that I can't draw to save my life and this thing needs some art like the Mona Lisa needs eyebrows. So I ask all of you talented, awesome people that can draw, be it in a sketchpad or in Photoshop, to help me and my plot bunny-provider out. Why do you need it to be drawn, you ask? Because the story's set back in Mr. Caan's Whooliganz' days (1992-93), and I can't find a picture of Alex from back then. Plus, Scott doesn't dress like Aunt Jemima any more, so I can't very well use my own photoshop skillz to make it look like he's in several different poses. Don't know what the hell I'm talking about when I say Whooliganz? Want a summary before you take the plunge? Follow the cut... See the dude on the left? That dude turns into this GQMF right here: Required viewing to get a feel for the AU Danny Williams that is the focal point of this story: And last but not least, the summary: September, 1992. After getting arrested for the last time, 15 year-old Danny Williams is sent to Hawaii via the government's new, Move it or Lose it program, which aims at correcting juvenile delinquents by taking them out of their environment and setting them up somewhere new. With his backwards jeans and baseball jerseys, his fondness for graffiti and weed, and that annoying habit of blasting House of Pain as loud as possible, Danny is a handful even for his uber-understanding foster parents. When he meets the KuKui High's newest and brightest student athlete, one Steve McGarrett, the two strike up an unlikely friendship that quickly turns into first love. As the school year winds down, and separation looms ever nearer, the boys decide to make their first (and last) summer together count for more than just teenage fun. Fast forward almost twenty years and two men meet in a garage, guns drawn, both after the same man, and neither recognizing the other until the dust settles...

Look what I won... Thank you to everyone involved in this story, and in this award. I couldn't have done it without y'all! For those that are wondering where I've disappeared to, I figured I should give a quick update. I'm working on TWO Big Bangs this year. One for J2 (for which the outline alone is pretty sizable) and one for my newest obsession McDanno, aka Danny and Steve of Hawaii Five O. So everything else is getting put on the back burner as far as other fics go until those are finished. Work has also been causing me a lot of grief. The hours I work tend to zap my energy and when I get home most nights, the last thing I want to do is make my brain work. Admittedly, there's been a lot of vegging out, doing nothing. I hope to get back into the swing of things this week, and get more written for each BB, so that I can finish up all the stories I've been teasing y'all with. I promise you, despite appearances, I have no intention of leaving any of them half-finished, but y'all have to be patient with me.

Who here is super and I mean SUPER good at photoshopping magazine covers and articles? The first issue would have both of them on the cover, and the article would focus on their individual styles as runners and also the result of the first race they run as part of the dynamic duo tour. Issue number two would again be both on the cover, this time focusing on the rest of the tour and how the two have started a relationship and how they 'found each other through running'.
